text:
 Select the oil. There are two possible essential oils that are appropriate for use on a turmeric stain - either eucalyptus oil or lavender oil. Use whichever you can source most easily. Massage the oil into the turmeric stain.  Wash the item of clothing as usual. Hang it out to dry, preferably in full sunlight. Once dry, check the item. If you can still see the remnants of a stain (these will probably be pink), try the following to get rid of the last bit:
